# Workflow preferences

- **Always commit** after completing a change — Rami's standing instruction
  ("we can always roll back from git"). Use concise, capitalized commit
  subjects matching the existing log style. Push to `origin main` after
  committing unless told otherwise.
- **Git remote is SSH** (`git@github.com:ramizil/<repo>.git`). This machine has
  no GitHub HTTPS credentials and no `gh` CLI — never switch remotes back to
  HTTPS; clone new repos with SSH URLs.
- **Secrets**: `.env` holds real API keys (Gemini, Cursor `crsr_...`, etc.).
  Never print key values to the terminal, commit them, or copy them into code.
  Only `.env.example` is tracked.
- **Cursor AI provider**: if AI calls fail with "Connection error … localhost:8080",
  the local proxy is down. Start it with:
  `CURSOR_API_KEY=<from .env> cursor-agent-api start 8080`
  (logs: `~/.cursor-agent-api/server.log`; `agent` CLI lives in `~/.local/bin`).
- **Language**: Rami writes in English and Hebrew; reply in the language he
  uses. User-facing AI artefacts are bilingual EN+HE unless specified.
